text: I see recipes for successfully running 'make node-sdk-unit-tests' on Windows 7 have rolled off the visible screen in this channel due to >10K messages.  Here is my latest recipe:
Incidentally, I re-cloned 'fabric' yesterday.  I synchronize fabric each time I start the VM, which I did about five times in two days working on this recipe:

make all   /* apparently not effective as I later had to make peer and make membersrvc*/
sudo npm install -g node-pre-gyp 

edit ..fabric/sdk/node/run-unit-test.sh add GOPATH and GOROOT to init()

make peer
make membersrvc

sudo bash
export GOPATH and GOROOT
make node-sdk-unit-tests
